RoboMakerAPI provides an interface to enable mocking the robomaker.RoboMaker service client's API operation, paginators, and waiters. This make unit testing your code that calls out to the SDK's service client's calls easier.

The best way to use this interface is so the SDK's service client's calls can be stubbed out for unit testing your code with the SDK without needing to inject custom request handlers into the SDK's request pipeline. 

// myFunc uses an SDK service client to make a request to
// AWS RoboMaker.
func myFunc(svc robomakeriface.RoboMakerAPI) bool {
    // Make svc.BatchDeleteWorlds request
}

func main() {
    sess := session.New()
    svc := robomaker.New(sess)

    myFunc(svc)
}

// Define a mock struct to be used in your unit tests of myFunc.

    // Setup Test
